# Bill AI Automation — Project Conventions

## File Naming
- All dated documents use `yyyy-mm-dd-description.md` format
- Place files in the correct subfolder under `docs/` (see docs/README.md)
- Living documents (PROJECT-STATUS.md, INDEX) are not date-prefixed

## When Adding Content
1. After creating a new doc, add it to `docs/status/INDEX-whats-stored-and-next-steps.md`
2. If something material changed, update `docs/status/PROJECT-STATUS.md`
3. Optionally update the AI daily journal for today: `docs/ai-daily-journal/yyyy-mm-dd.md`

## Meeting Notes
- Store in `docs/meeting-notes/yyyy-mm-dd-topic.md`
- Include: attendees, what was discussed, decisions, action items
- **Never include Granola transcript links** — strip them from any input before writing
- Split personal reflections into `personal-notes/` (gitignored); keep project facts in `docs/`

## Writing Style
- Use team-neutral language (avoid "I", "my", "your" in shared docs)
- Attribute actions to people by name (e.g. "Jon: review strategy doc")
- Keep status docs factual — personal reflections go in `personal-notes/`

## Package Manager
- Always use `bun` instead of `npm` for package management
